pouch boundary-line patch 0024 - CL-1a FS/process syscall wires.

The Clade arc (docs/LLVM-DESIGN.md) sub-chunk CL-1a: wire the pouch
FS/process syscalls that CL-0's census (LLVM-DESIGN.md section 16.1) found
clang/lld/make demand per-compile/per-link, each onto an EXISTING,
already-audited Thylacine kernel syscall (ZERO new kernel surface). The
0xFFFF ENOSYS sentinels these replace made every compile fail at
output-write (renameat), every header-search fail (getdents64), etc.

Wired (Linux name -> Thylacine kernel primitive):
  getpid    -> SYS_GETPID (72)         [temp-name mangling]
  chdir     -> SYS_CHDIR (69)          [make -C]     (kernel wants path+len)
  getcwd    -> SYS_GETCWD (70)         [cwd report]  (same (buf,size)->len)
  ftruncate -> SYS_WSTAT (59) SIZE     [lld output image sizing]
  fchmod    -> SYS_WSTAT (59) MODE
  fchmodat/chmod -> open(O_PATH)+SYS_WSTAT MODE   [path form]
  faccessat/access -> SYS_STAT (88) existence+owner-rwx probe
  renameat/rename  -> SYS_RENAME (57)  [PER-COMPILE: clang temp+atomic .o]
  unlinkat/unlink/rmdir -> SYS_UNLINK (58) (+REMOVEDIR)
  mkdirat/mkdir    -> SYS_WALK_CREATE (54) DMDIR   [make output dirs]
  readdir(DIR*)    -> SYS_READDIR (56) 9P-stream -> dirent translation
                                       [PER-COMPILE: header-search dir scan]
  open(O_CREAT)/openat -> SYS_WALK_CREATE (54)   [clang mkstemp +
                     the .o output; create-mode fopen; PER-COMPILE]

The FS-mutation kernel primitives (RENAME/UNLINK/WALK_CREATE) are
PARENT-FD + leaf-name, not path-based, so the *at functions split their
path into (parent-dir, leaf) via the new shared __pouch_open_parent
(src/fcntl/_pouch_fs.c + src/internal/_pouch_fs.h): open the parent O_PATH
(born R|W -- the A-1.7 navigation base the primitives accept; SYS_open
resolves it through stalk, cwd-joining a relative path, LS-4) and hand
(parent_fd, leaf) to the kernel. The /srv/ short-circuits in unlink()/
chmod() (0014) are preserved by delegating their real path to the CL-1a
*at variant. openat also lifts the stale "absolute-only" restriction
(CL-1a wired chdir/getcwd, so a relative path cwd-joins via SYS_open's
FROM_ROOT arm) and maps O_TRUNC -> +OTRUNC.

Deferred to CL-1b (not clean 1:1 wires -- ground truth from CL-0):
  - dup2/dup3: need dup-ONTO-a-chosen-fd; Thylacine SYS_DUP allocates a
    kernel-chosen slot (that is dup(), not dup2/dup3). The child's fd
    redirection maps onto the SYS_SPAWN_FULL_ARGV fd-list, not in-child
    dup2 -- posix_spawn territory.
  - pipe2: SYS_PIPE returns rd/wr in x0/x1 (a two-register svc return the
    single-return syscall() macro cannot capture) -- needs a small asm
    shim, landed with the process-substrate work.
  - posix_spawn / wait4: the audit-bearing process-lifecycle rewrite.

Invariants preserved:
  - P-1 (no foreign syscall numbers): every wire maps 1:1 onto a
    Thylacine kernel syscall (via the 0019 SYS_thyla_* self-contained
    define idiom -- aarch64 LP64 has no legacy aliases to repoint).
  - P-3 (no silently-wrong POSIX): AT_FDCWD-only forms reject a real
    dirfd with -ENOTSUP; a trailing-slash path -> -EINVAL; bounds ->
    -ENAMETOOLONG. No form silently misbehaves.
  - P-4 (boundary-line discipline): touches only the lower-half .c files
    + the two new pouch-internal files; the portable upper half and the
    public headers are untouched.

